  "prompt": "Are there any Nintendo Ds racing games that involves pit stop?",
  "response": "Yes, there are a few racing games for the Nintendo DS that involve pit stops. One notable title is:\n\n- **Mario Kart DS**: While not a traditional racing simulation, it features various tracks and mechanics where players can strategically use items and boost their performance. Pit stops aren't a core mechanic like in more simulation-focused racing games, but players can manage their items similar to managing race strategies.\n\nFor a more simulation-oriented experience, consider:\n\n- **Need for Speed: Nitro**: This title includes some elements of car modifications and tactics, though pit stops are not a core feature as seen in traditional racing simulations.\n\nWhile the DS is not primarily known for in-depth racing simulators, you might find similar mechanics in various racing games where strategy and management are essential.",
